Slice A Budget
Slice A Budget






					Having a monthly budget is the first step in taking control of your financial life. Learn how finding the right balance of spending and saving could help you grow your money for tomorrow.
				
Start by moving the slider to approximate your monthly income (after taxes).

The slider has a minimum value of $2000 and a maximum value of $20000. The current value is 
2,000
20,000










monthly income: 






Step 1 of 4
The  Must-Haves
Estimate the amount you would spend on housing, groceries, utilities, transportation, health insurance and everything else that's essential to your life each month.
Move slider to change percentage of monthly budget for this category.



Percent of monthly income spent on Must-Haves: 



Must-Haves



					Amount Allocated $500


					Amount remaining in monthly budget $4500





Step 2 of 4
The Nice-To-Haves
Now approximate your monthly spending on new clothes, dining out, movies and other ways to treat yourself to something extra.
Move slider to change percentage of monthly budget for this category.


 You have chosen 
10%for your Must-Haves.




