About Us




















Keystone Financial GroupWe are a fee based financial advisory firm assisting high net worth individuals and businesses with their financial objectives. 




Home
About Us
Services

Comprehensive Wealth Management
Investment Planning & Asset Management
Insurance Planning
Retirement Plan Services


Contact Us
About Us
Keystone Financial Group was founded by CPAs Rhonda Gilbert and Tom Savage in 1999 as an independently owned financial advisory firm. Their desire was to assist clients with all aspects of their financial lives by utilizing their vast experience in accounting and finance to help clients reach their financial goals.
Our primary goal is to help our clients manage their finances so they may retire comfortably.


Rhonda Gilbert, CPA
Rhonda is the Chief Executive Officer and co-founder of Keystone Financial Group. As an accounting and finance professional, Rhonda has over 30 years of experience. She has spoken at numerous associations and corporate functions regarding topics such as strategic financial planning for business owners, business succession, risk management strategies, and tax planning strategies.
Rhonda graduated with a degree in accounting from Georgia College & State University and currently lives in Marietta. Her son Andrew is also a member of the Keystone Financial Group team.

Tom Savage, CPA
Tom is co-founder and serves as the Chief Financial Officer of Keystone Financial Group. Tom handles many of the marketing functions for the firm including meeting with clients. Tom has over 25 years of accounting and finance experience and often works with clients to help them with financial issues such as retirement planning, risk management strategies, and strategic planning for business owners.
Tom is a graduate of Auburn University with a degree in accounting and currently lives in Suwanee.


Gary Fortier, CPA
Gary serves as the Chief Compliance Officer for Keystone Financial Group. Along with managing the day to day compliance and regulatory requirements for the firm, Gary also assists clients with their financial planning needs. This often includes cash flow projections and budgeting for small business owners, risk management and insurance solutions, and retirement planning needs.
Gary has over 20 years of experience and is also well versed when it comes to financial and accounting systems and how they can help benefit clients.
Gary graduated with a degree in accounting from Bentley College and currently resides in Marietta.

Andrew Gilbert, CFP®
Andrew serves as the Chief Investment Officer for Keystone Financial Group. As Chief Investment Officer, Andrew is responsible for designing and monitoring investment portfolios for clients based on their needs, goals, and personal financial situation.
Aside from closely monitoring client investments, Andrew also assists clients with retirement plan design and implementation for small business owners, investment taxation strategies, and general financial planning strategies.
He graduated with a BBA in Finance from Georgia Southern University in 2009 where he was also a member of the baseball team.  In 2011, he completed the financial planner program at Oglethorpe University in Atlanta. Andrew is a CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ professional and currently lives in Marietta.

Check the background of these investment professionals on FINRA’s BrokerCheck

Disclosures
The Company only transacts business in states where it is properly registered, or excluded or exempted from registration requirements.
Past performance may not be indicative of future results. Therefore no current or prospective client should assume that the future performance of any specific investment, investment strategy (Including the investments and/or investment strategies recommended and/or purchased by adviser), or product made reference to directly or indirectly on this website, or indirectly via link to any unaffiliated third party website, will be profitable or equal to corresponding indicated performance levels.
Different types of investment involve varying degrees of risk, and there can be no assurance that any specific investment will either be suitable or profitable for a client’s investment portfolio. No client or prospective client should assume that any information presented and/or made available on this website serves as a receipt of, or a substitute for, personalized individual advice from the advisor or any other investment professional.
Historical performance results for investment indexes and/or categories generally do not reflect the deduction of transaction and/or custodial charges or the deduction of an investment-management fee, the incurrence of which would have [the] effect of decreasing historical performance results.
